channel.title: Project-Complexity [Stable, Many bugs fixed, Good quality work]
channel.description:
[center][b]Hello,[/b]
[size=15pt][b]Info:[/b][/size] [i]So after long time of programming I decided to release my server to public. I have put a lot of work into it, so I hope to get some reputation and loads of comments. The original base is Ultimatium-X. This was hosted before and I had about 200players at one time, but I ran out of cash so decided to be a good person and release it to the community.[/i] [/center]
[center][size=20pt][b]Download:[/b][/size] [url=http://www.mediafire.com/?b3b2av16kwauy59][size=10pt][b]Server download[/b][/size][/url] [url=http://www.mediafire.com/?wavl6ba4d90c8dk][size=10pt][b]Client download[/b][/size][/url][/center]
[center][size=15pt][b]Features:[/b][/size][/center] [center]All skills working, with correct requirements, animations and other things Many minigames (Pest control, barrows, warriors-guild, fight pits, fight caves, barbarian assault) Specials fully working for many new weapons 700+ items Customizable client 700+ gfx and animations Redesigned shops Npcs spawned all across the map Fully working clipping Combat perfected Yell feature Correct food & pot delay 100% Mage bank + Near by areas features coded 100% Switching Auth code vote system And much more...[/center]

item.title: Project-Complexity [Stable, Many bugs fixed, Good quality work]
item.dc:creator: @arham_4 arham 4
item.description:
@arham_4 wrote:

I don’t see what you are listing…

You are listing [size=14pt]simple[/size] things that’s it. Anyone can add that agility course, anyone can say they have a better combat, anyone can say it’s more cleaner. If you cleaned, it’s probably just remove int a that you noticed isn’t used. Anyone can say they fixed bugs, anyone can say it’s more stable.

You list [size=14pt]npc spawns[/size]. Such a big deal?
You have listed [size=14pt]simple ActionHandler actions[/size]. Such a big deal?
You have listed [size=14pt]700+ items[/size]. Every server has that, it probably came with the server. Such a big deal?
You have listed [size=14pt]a redesigned shop[/size]? Redesigned = Deleted b and added b back. Or just adding a dot to the interface? Such a big deal?
You have listed [size=14pt]customizable client[/size]. Every server has it now… Such a big deal?
Yell feature, such a big deal?
[size=14pt]Specials fully working for many new weapons[/size]. Every server has this, probably came with the source… Such a big deal?
[size=14pt]100% Switching[/size], used from deception. Such a big deal?
[size=14pt]Combat perfected[/size], did you even touch the combathandler class? Such a big deal?
[size=14pt]All skills working, with correct requirements, animations and other things[/size], came with the source of course. Such a big deal?
[size=14pt]Fully working clipping[/size], got that from the source. Such a big deal?
[size=14pt]Many minigames (Pest control, barrows, warriors-guild, fight pits, fight caves, barbarian assault)[/size], all from original PI. Such a big deal?
[size=14pt]Funpk[/size]. Such a big deal?
[size=14pt]Giant mole[/size]. A simple npc spawn. Such a big deal?
[size=14pt]Skilling area[/size]. Simple adding objects and adding a simple teleTo command. Such a big deal?

And what I like…

[size=14pt]The background[/size].

THAT’S IT

All in all, looks like deception with a different client.

[hr]

If you actually did code all of this, then you should be able to answer this:

What makes .class files?
